The paper deals with coding schemes for thermal management of on-chip buses, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.AR). It also involves electrical engineering (cs.ET) and system design (cs.SY) aspects related to interconnect performance and power consumption. Additionally, the paper discusses error-correction techniques (cs.EM) for the transmitted information.
